Up for sale is my 1885 High Wall "winder" musket in 22lr.  It is a second variation coil spring action made in 1914.  All of the metal is in good original condition.  Bore is good/excellent.  The barrel has been tapped for the scope that is on it and there a few extra holes where another scope has been on it.  There is also a single hole on the very top of the receiver that I imagine served as a scope base also.  All of the holes are filled with the appropriate screws. It is clear and bright and works perfectly.  I also have a spare "Hotchkiss" rear sight that originally went with the first generation muskets but it also fits this one.

The sling swivel on the buttstock pulled out at some point and someone put in a nice repair and then covered all of the wood with a varnish. title: For Sale:  AR15...please read  the entire ad
location: South east-Oak Creek, South Milwaukee, Milwaukee, Wisconsin
postcontent:
This gun is priced this low because I know people have a bias against polymer lowers. I've owned Colt's, Rock River, LWRC and even the Bushmaster polymer (that one was bad). At be Waukesha gun show two years ago I bought the 2nd gen New Frontier complete lower after researching it and watching the videos on the website and reading the reviews. I built it with a Palmetto State Armory upper with the FN cold hammer forged 1/7 barrel, Midwest Industries railed free floated upper. I got the mil-spec BCG from joe bob outfitters and a BCM charging latch. I switched out the five dollar grip and stock with Magpul and added 'Magpul sights.

The first time out we pounded ten magazines through it and had zero issues. Last year it only went out twice and maybe had a few mags through each time. Round count is between 400-700... I'm sorry but I didn't keep a log. 

I have more than the 500 in the upper and parts alone, but I'll add a soft case two magazines and 60 rounds of ammo to get you going.

I'm hoping someone either gets this as a 1st rifle or if you have other ARs that you keep this one as is and shoot it before you switch out the New Frontier Lower. This gun has been accurate and reliable and I'll be happy to show the new owner range photos. I'm only selling because I have a needed home repair and I'm not selling the LWRC...lol.

Thanks for looking.
